---
title: Beef Ragu Rigatoni with Black Olive & Tomato Salsa
description: 'Al dente' is one of those phrases people throw around a lot when talking about pasta, but what does it actually mean? The Italian translates as 'to the tooth' and pasta cooked perfectly 'al dente' should still have a little bit of firmness. The way to tell is by biting through a piece - have a little nibble on one of this week's rigatoni before you serve up. If you can see thin centre of white in the middle of the cooked pasta then it's spot on and time to tuck in!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/beef-ragu-rigatoni-abba3da4.jpg
